snippet.textDisplay: kevin has always been one of my favourite artists since i was a teenager, his albums seemed to guide me along the roller coaster journey of growing into young adulthood, with each era seeming to be too perfectly in sync with how i was feeling and what i was going through at the time, and slow rush hasn’t fallen short of that. i’ve been so excited since the hiatus to finally experience tame live again - i bought tickets to 2 shows in canada, only now for the current global situation to lead me to returning back to aus... i was gutted! hoping that i can sell these tickets in canada so i can afford any tickets still available in aus - covid 19 has got me in the feels man

snippet.textDisplay:
It’s almost like Kevins performing in that imaginary place (the timeline in which no corona happened and tame impala continued touring) and we’re on the outside not being able to experience it fully but just thinking “man it would have been so cool to experience!”

-I usually don’t buy concert tickets, and quite frankly it would’ve been my second concert ever going to if the touring stopped, I got one for me and my girlfriend (we’re in a long distance relationship, about 5 hours away and Kevin’s music is our absolute favorite, but sadly corona happened! I have faith we’ll get to experience his masterpiece live one day, I have recurring dreams of being at the concert at least once a week; and when I wake up I get sad and call my girlfriend and we then listen to slow rush afterwards, I know these are weird times for everyone, but I’m thankful we have this beautiful album to listen to! when everything comes back to normal I hope to experience the dream in real life and it won’t be so imaginary! 😊🙏🏻
